Kim Jong Il Enjoys Performance Given by Russian Dancing Troupe 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il appreciated a performance given by the State Academy Beryozka Dancing Troupe of Russia Named after N.S. Nadezhdina on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il was greeted at a theatre by Mira Koltsova, head of the dancing troupe, and Alexander Matsegora, Russian charge d' affaires ad interim here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il expressed thanks to the artistes of the dancing troupe for encouraging the Korean people in their drive to greet the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK with shining labor achievements through their enthusiastic performances and had a cordial talk with the Russian guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dancing troupe with a long history and tradition raised the curtain with chorus "Song of General Kim Jong Il." It staged colorful numbers such as female group dance "Beryozka", male group dance "Jokers", mixed group dances "In Memory of the Defenders of the Motherland" and "Vast Plain", comic dance "Old Bachelors", solo dance "Recollection", dance suite "This Happened Long Ago," songs and dances "Beryozka", "The Evening in the Suburbs of Moscow", "Katyusha" and "Flower-Strewn Brink of Marsh" from the revolutionary opera "Tell the Story, Forest".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their performance the artistes truthfully represented the Russian people's ardent love for the country, optimistic and diligent life and national custom with refined artistry and graceful and enthusiastic rhythms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance closed with chorus of Korean song "The General of Korea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He congratulated the artistes on their successful performance and extended his greetings to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the dancing troupe, reflecting the unanimous reverence of all the artistes for him, expressed warmest thanks to him for watching their performance and showing deep interest in their art creation activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the C.C., the WPK, Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su, servicepersons, creators and artistes of the army and society.

Congratulations to PM of Lebanon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a congratulatory message to Fouad Sanyora on his reappointment as Prime Minister of Lebanon on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished the Prime Minister success in his work for the stability and prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun sent a similar message to Fouzi Salloukh on his reappointment as minister of Foreign Affairs and Immigrants on the same day.

Military Attaches Corps Visits Panmunjom 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kaesong July 17 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited Panmunjom Thursday on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War.
 They went round the monument bearing the inscription of autograph of President Kim Il Sung erected to convey the immortal exploits performed by him in the sacred cause of reunifying the country, the room where the armistice talks took place, the hall where the Armistice Agreement was signed and the conference room of the former Military Armistice Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Miguel Angel Gala Valiente, military attache of the Cuban embassy, wrote in the visitor's book that whenever he visited Panmunjom he keenly realized the wise leadership the President provided for beating back the U.S. imperialists' armed invasion and leading the Fatherland Liberation War to victory, adding that the feats he performed by winning the victory in the war would last forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alexei Bartusov, military attache of the Russian embassy, said that the Korean people have undergone indescribable misfortune and pain due to the national split, hoping that Korea would be reunified without delay. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sun Yanfeng, military, naval and air attache of the Chinese embassy, said he hoped that the army and people of the DPRK would register greater successes in socialist construction and in the efforts to accomplish the cause of national reunification under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, supreme commander of the Korean People's Army.

Cuban Embassy Officials Visit Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Palace 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- Enrique Montoto Cruz, Cuban charge d'affaires ad interim, and staff members of the Cuban embassy here visited the Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Palace on Thursday on the occasion of the month of solidarity with the Cuban people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Being briefed on the fact that the palace was successfully built into a centre for the extracurricular education of the rising generation and has made a great contribution to educating young people under the great loving care of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, the guests looked round rooms for various hobby groups at the palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they appreciated a performance given by members of the art group of the palace.

Single-minded Unity Brings Victory 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are now energetically hastening the building of a great, prosperous and powerful socialist nation with the might of single-minded unity around the Workers' Party of Korea and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The tradition of this unity was established at the dawn of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The young communists of new generation in the early days ushered in the proud origin of single-minded unity, holding President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the centre of unity and cohesion and the sun of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They defended this unity and cohesion with their own lives, not flinching even on the gallows, and handed it down to the posterity as a precious asset. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The unity and cohesion achieved by them was the guarantee for the victory of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and the solid foundation stone of single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Carrying forward this tradition of great unity, the second generation of the Korean revolution won brilliant victories in the grim Fatherland Liberation War (June 25, 1950 - July 27, 1953) and in the arduous postwar rehabilitation and construction and socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The third and fourth generations, the main force of the revolution today, following the example of the previous generations, are giving an unswerving continuity to single-minded unity, closely rallied around General Secretary Kim Jong Il as Songun revolutionary comrades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The might of this single-minded unity underlies the world-startling miracles in history that the Korean people have wrought in the struggle to defend the country and achieve national prosperity through centuries, tiding over tests and troubles which any revolution and people had never undergone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Pessimism and vacillation was a thing unknown to the Korean people even in face of the stifling maneuvers of the imperialists, natural disasters in consecutive years and immeasurable economic hardships. Rallied around General Secretary Kim Jong Il with a single heart, they withstood the "Arduous March" and forced march and emerged the honorable victor in the fight to defend socialism.

U.S. Policy of Bolstering Armed Forces Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The U.S. policy of bolstering armed forces is the root cause of arms race and nuclear threat. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its talk about "potential enemy" and "means to deter attack" is nothing but sophism intended to hasten the modernization of nukes and the development of new type weapons, the article notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citing concrete facts to prove that the U.S. is pushing forward the modernization of nukes behind the curtain of "nuclear disarmament," the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is steadily developing and manufacturing new type nukes, while warning other countries not to develop and possess nukes. This is a gangster-like behavior. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is chiefly to blame for sparking off a new Cold War and arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces are working in real earnest to build missile shields, regarding a preemptive missile attack as the main thrust of its military strategy in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The increased spurs put by the U.S. to building missile shields and modernizing nukes and other military equipment would only compel other countries to take corresponding measures against them. Consequently, these moves will escalate the arms race and the danger of nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean Peninsula is fraught with the greatest danger of a nuclear war in the world at present. The U.S. warlike forces are stepping up the production of latest type weapons while amassing war forces in the areas around the Korean Peninsula for the purpose of igniting another Korean war, with a hue and cry over the non-existent "military threat" from the DPRK. It is their strategic aim to ignite a nuclear war in Korea and escalate it into the areas around it in a bid to conquer Asia and realize its ambition for world domination. The U.S. has already made public its scenario for a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK as a prelude to its nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces are getting frantic with arms race and nuclear arms buildup at a time when the world people are making positive efforts to create a peaceful environment. This is a blatant challenge to the desire of humankind for peace and an act of seriously threatening and disturbing world peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their reckless arms buildup and moves for aggression are increasing the danger of war and putting peace, security and stability in the world at great peril. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They would be well advised to drop their foolish ambition to dominate the world with an upper-hand of strength and swim with the trend of the times towards peace and disarmament.

All Koreans Called upon to Remain True to Idea of "By Our Nation Itself" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The militant slogan "Open up a new era of independent reunification and peace and prosperity by pooling the efforts of our nation!" laid down in the joint editorial for this year has powerfully encouraged all the compatriots in the sacred patriotic struggle for the reunification of the country as it reflects the requirements of the era and the aspiration of the nation. Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should enshrine the idea of "By our nation itself" as their faith and intensify the movement for national reunification, guided by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should uphold the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration whose justice and vitality have been proved in practice and thoroughly implement them and thus independently achieve the country's reunification in the spirit of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to eradicate the source of war and achieve durable peace on the Korean Peninsula and attain the development and prosperity common to the nation. Peace and prosperity present themselves as historic tasks to be achieved without fail to accelerate the cause of the country's reunification and carve out a bright future of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak group is keen to obliterate the idea of "By our nation itself" and stem the trend of the times towards independent reunification and peace and prosperity. Its treacherous and anti-reunification true colors have been fully revealed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that it is impossible to successfully usher in the new era of independent reunification and peace and prosperity as long as the Lee group hell bent on flunkeyism towards the U.S., anti-reunification acts and confrontation with compatriots is allowed to betray the nation any longer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Koreans are to implement the above-said slogan to the letter, they should intensify the nationwide struggle to smash the vicious anti-reunification acts of the Lee clique of traitors, first of all.

Candlelight Action Staged in Seoul against Japan's Move to Grab Tok Islet
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- Citizens from all walks of life in south Korea waged a candlelight action in Seoul on July 14 in protest against Japan's move to grab Tok Islet and the Lee Myung Bak group's sycophancy and treachery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citizens held a candlelight rally in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul condemning Japan for its bid to grab Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally branded Japan's distortion of history and assertion of its dominion over Tok Islet as an action to revive militarism, vowing to hold higher candlelight in protest against Japan's move to usurp part of the territory of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Denouncing the security authorities for trying to arrest a citizen involved in the just struggle against the brazen-faced action of the Japanese government after labeling it "illegal," they stated if Lee quelled the voices of the people, he would certainly allow Japan to grab Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They pelted eggs at the Japanese embassy in token of protest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In another development, at least 400 persons of culture and art and citizens staged a candlelight rally against the import of American beef in Chonggye plaza and conducted information services condemning the group of traitors for their sycophantic act of selling off the sovereignty of the people to the foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon hearing the news of the police crackdown upon the candlelight action in front of the above-said embassy while the rally was under way, its participants rushed there past the police cordon to join in the candlelight action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day rallies took place on Tok Islet and Ullung Island of Ullung County, North Kyongsang Province in protest against the Japanese reactionaries' move to grab the islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Teachers' Union of south Korea released a statement on the same day demanding Japan halt at once its brazen-faced and aggressive bid to grab the islet and the Lee "government" take the earliest possible steps against Japan's above-mentioned bid.

U.S. Deploys Carrier Task Force in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist aggression troops are deploying aircraft carrier task force in south Korea, according to a military source. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Super-large nuclear carrier Reagan already entered Pusan Port to be followed by the entry of a guided missile destroyer into Phyongthaek Port on July 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warmongers of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces are also contemplating bringing guided missile destroyers and subs to Jinhae Port and other major ports in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is the fact that the U.S. imperialists deployed the task force and opened it to media to kick off a racket, timed to coincide with Hwarang war exercises being conducted by the south Korean puppet army, local administrative organs, police and reserve forces on the land under a coordinated operation and naval landing operational exercises now underway almost everyday in the area of Phohang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is nothing but a premeditated move to put into practice the scheme to preempt the strike at the DPRK while militarily threatening it behind the scenes of "dialogue and negotiations."

Kim Jong Il's Work off Press in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" was brought out in booklet by the Nakhodka Format Publishing House of Russia on July 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on August 4, Juche 86 (1997) deals with the immortal feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in the cause of national reunification and formulates the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo as the three charters for national reunification. It also indicates the tasks to be fulfilled to accomplish the cause of national reunification on the basis of them and ways to do so.

Kim Il Sung Remembered in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- Reading sessions on the reminiscences of President Kim Il Sung "With the Century" and photo exhibitions were held by the Secretariat of the Pan-African Movement and in Uganda, round-table talks in Mexico and Uganda and film shows in Indonesia and Russia on July 7 and 8 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the photo exhibitions were photos showing the revolutionary careers and exploits of Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director for Political Affairs and International Relations of the Pan-African Movement and the chief of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Comrade Kim Il Sung of Old Kampala Higher Middle School said: The President was born in a revolutionary family. He was a peerlessly great man who devoted all his life to accomplishing the just cause of the Korean people and world revolutionary people since he embarked on the road of struggle in his teens. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The coordinator of the National Coordinating Committee of the Workers' Party of Mexico highly praised the President for dedicating his all to the victory of the Korean revolution and the world revolution, the human cause of independence and the development of the world socialist movement, adding that the exploits performed by the President would shine forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has successfully carried forward the revolutionary idea and cause of the President and is leading it to completion. All the revolutionaries in the world are highly proud and honored to see the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people advancing under the uplifted socialist banner, true to his Songun leadership. Progressive mankind is looking up to socialist Korea as a beacon of hope. No force on earth can match the strength of the DPRK.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Demise Commemorated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The Group of Youth for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea in Vienna, Austria, issued its bulletin on July 8 to commemorate the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 It carried an article titled "Revolutionary Career of President Kim Il Sung" with a portrait of the smiling President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  In the article the bulletin noted that the President founded the Anti-Japanese People's Guerrilla Army and waged the arduous 15-year-long anti-Japanese armed struggle to realize the historic cause of national liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the liberation of Korea he successfully realized the cause of building the party, the army and the country, led the Fatherland Liberation War and the postwar rehabilitation and construction to victory and built a powerful socialist country, independent in politics, self-supporting in the economy and self-reliant in national defence, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that the President has been praised as the prominent statesman and the great leader by not only the Korean people but also the world people.

Struggle of S. Korean People Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- Koreans in the United States held a candlelight meeting in Los Angeles on July 11 in support of the struggle of the south Korean people opposing the import of American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting charged that though apprehension about "the mad cow disease" is growing in the U.S. where cattle aging less than 20 months only is allowed to be used for food, the Lee Myung Bak "government" has decided to import the beef of cattle aging even more than 30 months. This is behavior of disregarding the people's health at all, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dismissing Lee's attempt to save the situation by means of replacing some ministers as a deceptive trick, they held that all the people should pool their efforts to struggle against the south Korean authorities' moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They urged the south Korean authorities to stop crackdown on the members of the People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Markets to American Beef and come out to the total renegotiations on the beef import. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the participants in the meeting conducted information activities, distributing the handbills referring to the danger of the "mad cow disease."

Struggle against Lee Myung Bak's Anti-Reunification Moves Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 17 (KCNA) -- The Federation of Koreans in Australia issued an appeal on July 10 urging the vigorous struggle against the anti-reunification moves of the south Korean ruling forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal said that they can no longer tolerate the anti-DPRK moves of traitor Lee Myung Bak seeking to annul the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, its action program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It dismissed his call on "the north to dismantle its nukes first" as reckless remarks of a political idiot, who does not know even about the circumstances and essence of the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula and origin of nuclear threat, and a revelation of his idea of slavish subordination to America. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called for smashing the above-said moves through struggle and frustrating the anachronistic and risky military provocations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that the overseas compatriots should conduct a vigorous drive to realize the independent reunification of the country, holding higher the banner of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration.

Rusia: impresa obra de Kim Jong Il en folleto
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 17 de julio (ATCC) -- La Editorial Nakhodka Format de Rusia dio a luz el dia 8 en folleto la obra del Dirigente Kim Jong Il "Materialicemos de modo consecuente el legado del gran Lider, camarada Kim Il Sung para la reunificacion de la patria", publicada el 4 de agosto del 86 (1997) de la Era Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta obra enumera las hazanas realizadas por el Presidente Kim Il Sung para el cumplimiento de la causa de reunificacion de la patria y formula como Tres Cartas para la Reunificacion de la Patria los 3 Principios de la Reunificacion de la Patria, el Programa de Diez Puntos de la Gran Unidad Pannacional y el Proyecto de Fundacion de Republica Federal Democratica de Coryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Igualmente, aclara las tareas y remedios para el cumplimiento de dicha causa, que se basan en las 3 cartas mencionadas.

Cuerpo de Agregados Militares en Corea visita Phanmunjom
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kaesong, 17 de julio (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 55o aniversario del triunfo del pueblo coreano en la Guerra de Liberacion de la Patria, el Cuerpo de Agregados Militares en Corea visito este jueves Phanmunjom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los huespedes recorrieron el monumento a la firma autografa del Presidente Kim Il Sung, que transmite sus imborrables hazanas realizadas en la sagrada causa para la reunificacion de la patria, la sala de negociaciones de armisticio, la de suscripcion del acuerdo de armisticio y la sala de reuniones de la ex comision militar de armisticio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El agregado militar cubano, Miguel Angel Gala Valiente, escribio en el libro de visitas que cada vez que visita este lugar, se siente profundamente impresionado de la sabia direccion del camarada  Kim Il Sung quien condujo a la victoria la guerra de liberacion de la patria frustrando la invasion armada del imperialismo yanqui y anadio que seran eternas sus hazanas realizadas por la victoria en la guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El agregado militar ruso Alexei Bartusov y el chino Sun Yanfeng senalaron que la division nacional hace sufrir al pueblo coreano indecibles desgracias y penalidades y desearon que bajo la sabia direccion del Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea Kim Jong Il, el ejercito y el pueblo de Corea logren mayores exitos en la construccion socialista y el cumplimiento de la causa de reunificacion de la patria.
